  "issue_title": "[Bug] Extensionless configured files like Dockerfile and Makefile are skipped as unsupported",
  "issue_body": "## Description\n\nToken/base scoring derives `FileChange.file_extension` from the basename only when the filename contains a dot. Extensionless files such as `Dockerfile` and `Makefile` therefore get `file_extension == \"\"`.\n\nThat empty extension causes `calculate_token_score_from_file_changes()` to treat the file as unsupported and return `skipped-unsupported`, even though `programming_languages.json` explicitly configures `dockerfile` and `makefile` as supported tree-sitter languages.\n\nThis means PRs that only or mostly modify Dockerfiles or Makefiles can be silently under-scored despite those file types being configured.\n\n## Steps to Reproduce\n\n1. Create a `FileChange` for `Dockerfile` with valid Dockerfile content.\n2. Run `calculate_token_score_from_file_changes()` with the normal token and language configs.\n3. Observe that `file_extension == \"\"` and the file result uses `skipped-unsupported`.\n4. Compare with `programming_languages.json`, where `dockerfile` is configured with `language: \"dockerfile\"`.\n\n## Expected Behavior\n\nConfigured extensionless filenames such as `Dockerfile`, `dockerfile`, `Makefile`, and `makefile` should normalize to `dockerfile` and `makefile`, then use the configured scoring path.\n\nNormal dotted filenames such as `build.mk` should keep their existing extension behavior, and unrelated extensionless files such as `README` should remain unsupported unless configured.\n\n## Actual Behavior\n\n`Dockerfile`, `dockerfile`, `Makefile`, and `makefile` normalize to an empty extension and are skipped as unsupported, producing no token/base score contribution from those files.\n\n## Environment\n\n- OS: N/A\n- Python version: N/A\n- Commit/Version: current `test` branch\n\n## Additional Context\n\nRelevant code:\n\n- `gittensor/classes.py` \u2014 `FileChange._calculate_file_extension()` returns `\"\"` for basenames without `.`\n- `gittensor/validator/utils/tree_sitter_scoring.py` \u2014 uses `file.file_extension` to decide whether a file is supported\n- `gittensor/validator/weights/programming_languages.json` \u2014 contains configured entries for `dockerfile` and `makefile`\n\nLocal proof before the fix:\n\n```text\nDockerfile current ext '' method skipped-unsupported score 0.0 nodes 0\nDockerfile forced ext 'dockerfile' method tree-diff score 0.0 nodes 7\nMakefile current ext '' method skipped-unsupported score 0.0 nodes 0\nMakefile forced ext 'makefile' method tree-diff score 0.0 nodes 3\n",
  "merged_at": "2026-05-10T21:45:35Z",
